I"ÿ<p>The short answer is yes. Mosquitoes do exhibit blood-sucking preferences, say the experts. ‚ÄúOne in 10 people are highly attractive to mosquitoes,‚Äù reports Jerry Butler, PhD, professor emeritus at the University of Florida. But it‚Äôs not dinner they‚Äôre sucking out of you. Female mosquitoes ‚Äì males do not bite people ‚Äì need human blood to develop fertile eggs. And apparently, not just anyone‚Äôs will do.</p>

