<p>Who mosquitoes like best
Although researchers have yet to pinpoint what mosquitoes consider an ideal hunk of human flesh, the hunt is on. ‚ÄúThere‚Äôs a tremendous amount of research being conducted on what compounds and odors people exude that might be attractive to mosquitoes,‚Äù says Joe Conlon, PhD, technical advisor to the American Mosquito Control Association. With 400 different compounds to examine, it‚Äôs an extremely laborious process. ‚ÄúResearchers are just beginning to scratch the surface,‚Äù he says.</p>

